<head>
<title>ON TAX FREEDOM DAY, ACU URGES 16TH AMENDMENT REPEAL</title>
</head>

<body>

For Immediate Release<br>
May 16, 1996<br>
Contact: Jeff Hollingsworth<br>
(703) 836-8602<p>

<center>
<h2>FLAT TAX, SALES TAX, WHATEVER: FOCUS MUST STAY ON<br>
JUNKING CURRENT NIGHTMARISH TAX SYSTEM, ACU SAYS </h2>
</center>

<p>
WASHINGTON, D.C.--- "Some conservatives favor a flat tax, others support a national sales or
value-added tax, still others have different ideas on how best to pay for the legitimate
functions of government. The main thing is, we must not allow differences over those approaches
from causing the tax reform movement to lose sight of the real goal: elimination of the current
Federal income tax non-system, with its enormous bureaucracy, byzantine rules and regulations,
and abuses and outrages. That's why ACU is happy to join forces with those who also recognize
the importance of staying focused on the larger objective," said David A. Keene, Chairman of the
American Conservative Union (ACU), at a "Commitment to Tax Reform" press conference in
Washington, D.C., hosted by Citizens for a Sound Economy.
<P>
     "This year's Tax Freedom Day- - May 7 - - was the latest ever," Keene continued. "When you
add in the hidden costs of government, such as regulations and other expensive burdens,
Americans must labor until July 3 before they're in the clear and able to keep all of what they
work hard to earn. That's an outrage to cause every American's blood to boil. The 105th Congress
cannot allow this level and scope of taxation to continue. The current tax structure is
hopelessly beyond repair and the only sane, fair thing to do is scrap it entirely.
<P>
     "ACU has already launched its own long-term project with the objective of abolishing the
IRS and repealing the 16th Amendment, which authorized the Federal income tax. Yet that does not
mean we cannot join with our friends who argue persuasively for a flat tax in saying with them
that what exists now is a nightmare that must end and that the American people deserve tax
justice," Keene concluded. "The issue is no longer whether or not to end taxation as we know it,
but how soon we will get there. Once we get there, we may find that a flat tax is the way to go,
or that the best option is the national sales tax, or that some other approach is better.
Whatever the outcome, we simply must not lose sight of the objective, we simply must not let
Congress dodge the issue any longer, and we simply must make sure that the American people don't
stop pressing for reform."
<P>
     The American Conservative Union, founded in 1964, is the country's oldest grassroots
conservative lobbying organization. On behalf of its nearly one million members and supporters,
it lobbies on a wide range of issues before the Congress.

                              -30-  


<P>

1007 Cameron Street, Alexandria, VA 22314<br>
PHONE: (703) 836-8602 FAX: (703) 836-8608<br>
E-Mail: <a href="mailto:acu@conservative.org">acu@conservative.org</a> WWW: <a href="http://www.conservative.org">http://www.conservative.org</a><p>

[ <a href="/conservative/">ACU Home Page</a> ]
</body>
</html> 
