micromanage a system of 800,000 employees. Nobody has that kind of span 
of control. So what you want to do is have lots of smaller units. You 
want to constantly devolve things away, get them back to somebody who can 
actually do something. A healthy, productive system is best educated and 
shaped by markets. I'm lost. What are you doing? Let me go back and try 
