<TITLE>THOMAS SHEEHY -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>THOMAS SHEEHY</H3>
<B>JAY KINGHAM FELLOW IN INTERNATIONAL REGULATORY AFFAIRS</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/sheehy.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Sheehy examines issues relating to the regulatory aspects of international trade, including intellectual property rights, and matters related to the United Nations and development aid. Sheehy is co-author of Heritage's <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/econ_index/toc.html.cgi">Index of Economic Freedom</a>, a global score card on the relative level of economic freedom in over 142 countries. He previously served as Heritage's African and Third World Affairs Analyst, and worked for Kumasi Brewing Ltd. in Ghana. Sheehy is a doctoral candidate at the University of Virginia, where he earned his M.A. in foreign affairs.

